article.headline: Rice 62, Houston 52
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Michael Harris had 22 points and was one of three Rice players in double figures as the Owls beat Houston 62-52 on Wednesday night. Jason McKrieth scored 13 points and Brock Gillespie added 10 for Rice (4-1). The Owls shot 50 percent (14-of-21) and had 10 steals, eight by Rashid Smith. Houston (0-2) trailed 27-24 at halftime, and Rice opened the second half with an 11-0 run. A jumper by Brock Gillespie gave Rice it's biggest lead at 53-38 with 6:47. The Cougars responded with a 12-2 run to make it 55-50 with 3:56 remaining. Rice then outscored Houston 7-2 to seal the win. Andre Owens led the Tigers with 25 points. Lanny Smith scored 11 points and Anwar Owens grabbed 10 rebounds.
